{
  "texts": [
    "In summary, by merging LLM training techniques with Dewey's moral philosophy, we propose a moral growth model for LLMs, as illustrated in Fig. 1.",
    "However, as the next section will soon reveal, this model shows an idealized trajectory of LLMs' moral development, with the final stage remaining unachievable at present.",
    "This highlights the limitations of the current AI alignment approach and the potential risks it may encounter.",
    "Firstly, though RLHF represents OpenAI's approach to alignment and is one of the pathways to enhance the moral competence of LLMs, it has not yet achieved the level of Deweyan character.",
    "In Dewey's moral philosophy, character is based on advanced self and reflective capabilities."
  ]
}